6:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-12","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Rate Mechanics"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Both Bitget and KuCoin use 8-hour funding intervals with standard premium/discount calculations based on perpetual-spot price differentials. Bitget tends to have more volatile funding rates due to its copy trading features driving concentrated positions, while KuCoin maintains steadier rates through its diverse altcoin ecosystem. Both exchanges cap funding rates at ±0.75% per interval. Bitget's newer perpetual contracts often show higher initial funding volatility compared to KuCoin's established markets."}]]}]
7:["$","$Lb",null,{"items":[{"question":"Which exchange has better funding rate stability?","answer":"KuCoin generally offers more stable funding rates due to its mature user base and diverse trading patterns. Bitget's copy trading features can create concentrated positions leading to more volatile funding rates, especially on newer listings."},{"question":"How do funding rate caps compare between platforms?","answer":"Both exchanges cap funding rates at ±0.75% per 8-hour interval. However, Bitget more frequently hits these caps on popular altcoin perpetuals due to its retail-heavy copy trading ecosystem creating imbalanced long/short ratios."},{"question":"Which platform is better for altcoin perpetual arbitrage?","answer":"Bitget offers faster new token listings with initially volatile funding rates, creating short-term arbitrage opportunities. KuCoin provides broader altcoin perpetual selection with more predictable funding patterns for systematic strategies."},{"question":"Are there differences in funding rate calculation methods?","answer":"Both use identical calculation methodologies based on premium/discount to spot indices. The main difference lies in execution - Bitget's copy trading can amplify funding rate swings while KuCoin's diverse user base creates more balanced funding environments."}]}]
